                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/4407: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Barcelona</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Barcelona</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-01-18T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >January 18, 1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Yesterday personally observed contingent of American, German and English
                    volunteers. Americans numbering about 40 headed the column and carried a red
                    flag marked American battalion.</p>
                <p>As circumstances may render advisable statutes named in the Department’s January
                    13, 7 p.m., will be brought to the attention of American citizens.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
